        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-19T18:23:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is the last field before the start of the data. Every refactoring use case that I\u0027ve planned to use GrBlockAllocator in, the wrapping types need a small amount of per-block storage. Often this is tracking some sort of live count, as in GrMemoryPool, but it may represent a last-allocated offset, or last-offset to something that needs a destructor invoked.\n\nTheoretically, the wrapping classes could always make their own initial allocation for this metadata, but having a field that would always start at 0 and be available ended up being very convenient.",
      "parentUuid": "7fc25c9c_7b9db541",
      "range": {
